-- BP Contractor Killed in Construction Accident at Refinery in Rotterdam
-- John Buckley
-- 2010-06-16T09:49:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-16/bp-contractor-killed-in-construction-accident-at-its-rotterdam-refinery.html

          
          
             BP Plc  said a worker was killed in a
construction accident today at the U.K. companyâ€™s refinery in
Rotterdam.  
 The man, employed by Mourik, a construction company
contracted by BP, was crushed by a piece of concrete foundation
that was being moved at the site, BP spokesman Carlo Eijkels
said by telephone today.  
 Local broadcaster RTV Rijnmond reported that the building
material fell from a crane. The refinery is able to  process 
400,000 barrels of oil a day.  
